{{Portuguese name|Soares|Camacho}} {{Infobox football biography |name = Rafael Camacho |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Rafael Euclides Soares Camacho |birth_date = {{birth date and age|2000|5|22|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Lisbon]], Portugal |height = {{convert|1.75|m|abbr=on}} |position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]] |currentclub = [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] |clubnumber = 64 |youthyears1 = 2008–2013 |youthclubs1 = [[Sporting CP]] |youthyears2 = 2013–2016 |youthclubs2 = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] |youthyears3 = 2016 |youthclubs3 = → [[Real S.C.]] (Loan) |youthyears4 = 2016–2019 |youthclubs4 = [[Liverpool F.C. Reserves and Academy|Liverpool]] | years1 = 2019– | clubs1 = [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] | caps1 = 1 | goals1 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2015-2016 | nationalteam1 = [[Portugal national under-16 football team|Portugal U16]] | nationalcaps1 = 6 | nationalgoals1 = 2 | nationalyears2 = 2016-2017 | nationalteam2 = [[Portugal national under-17 football team|Portugal U17]] | nationalcaps2 = 6 | nationalgoals2 = 4 | nationalyears3 = 2018 | nationalteam3 = [[Portugal national under-18 football team|Portugal U18]] | nationalcaps3 = 1 | nationalgoals3 = 2 |club-update = 18:32, 19 January 2019 (UTC) }} '''Rafael Euclides Soares Camacho''' (born 22 May 2000) is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/rafael-euclides-soares-camacho/455763/|title=Portugal - Rafael Camacho - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway|website=Uk.soccerway.com|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref>
==Career== A Portugal U17 international, Camacho joined Liverpool’s academy from [[Sporting CP|Sporting Lisbon]] at the end of the 2015–16 season following a successful trial. He is a versatile player who can play anywhere across the front line but had also featured at right back and wing back.<ref>[http://www.liverpoolfc.com/team/academy/player/rafael-camacho] {{dead link|date=January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/liverpool-no-rush-make-rafa-15620877|title=The latest on Rafa Camacho's Liverpool future|first=James|last=Pearce|date=2 January 2019|website=Liverpoolecho.co.uk|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref>
Camacho was named on the [[Substitute (association football)|substitutes]]' bench for the [[Merseyside Derby]] against [[Everton F.C. |Everton]] in the [[Premier League]] on 7 April 2018 as a late injury replacement for [[Alberto Moreno]] but did not make an appearance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/jamespearceecho/status/982576591699152896?s=21|title=Rafa Camacho now on the bench for #LFC. Moreno suffering with a thigh injury in the warm up|first=James|last=Pearce|date=7 April 2018|publisher=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref> In December 2018 he was named on the bench for [[Premier League]] games against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] and [[Manchester United]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/sporting-cp-make-loan-move-for-liverpools-rafa-camacho/9y0hk5h1mcs21tckaz4mtbzr2|title=Liverpool transfer news: Sporting Lisbon make loan move for Rafa Camacho|website=Goal.com|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref> He made his senior debut in the [[FA Cup]] third round against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] on 7 January 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/01/07/england/fa-cup/wolverhampton-wanderers-fc/liverpool-fc/2943531/|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers vs. Liverpool - 7 January 2019 - Soccerway|website=Uk.soccerway.com|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/liverpool-teenagers-rafael-camacho-curtis-13825739|title=Liverpool teenagers handed full debuts in FA Cup clash|last=Prenderville|first=Liam|date=2019-01-07|website=mirror|access-date=2019-01-08}}</ref> He made his league debut 12 days later, coming on as a late substitute in a 4–3 win over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/335036-jurgen-klopp-rafael-camacho-crystal-palace|title=Klopp: I told Rafa he'd made the most important challenge of his life!|publisher=Liverpool Football Club|last=Carroll|first=James|date=21 January 2019|accessdate=21 January 2019}}</ref>
==Personal life== Camacho is of [[Angola|Angolan]] descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://novojornal.co.ao/desporto/interior/angolano-de-17-anos-na-equipa-principal-do-liverpool-42299.html|title=Angolano de 17 anos na equipa principal do Liverpool|website=Novo Jornal|language=pt|access-date=2019-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/interior/rafael-camacho-o-black-ronaldo-esta-a-caminho-do-sporting-10387915.html|title=Rafael Camacho. O 'Black Ronaldo' está a caminho do Sporting|website=www.dn.pt|language=pt|access-date=2019-01-08}}</ref>
